        <abstract> 
<p>CD’s sons tell him that Samuel Butler in <hi rend="italic">Unconscious memory</hi> states that some passages in <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi> were taken from his <hi rend="italic">Evolution, old and new</hi>. Their unprejudiced view is that the passages do come from Butler. CD hopes EK will give a clear explanation if he writes on the matter in <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi>.</p> 
            <p>CD is taking no public notice of Butler’s attack on himself.</p>
        </abstract>
